About the job
TheSoul Publishing is one of the largest digital media publishers in the world, producing entertaining and positive online content for more than 2 billion followers across the globe. We are the team behind channels like 5-Minute Crafts, Bright Side, and many others across YouTube, TikTok, Instagram, and Facebook.
We are currently looking for a tech-savvy Analyst Intern to join our IT team remotely. This internship is ideal for someone passionate about AI tools and digital innovation, with a keen analytical mind and strong curiosity for exploring how modern technologies can improve media production and operations.

What you will do:
Support operational activities across ongoing and upcoming projects;
Research and evaluate AI-based tools such as video analysers, text-to-video platforms, and other automation solutions;
Assist in gathering requirements from stakeholders and organising them into structured documentation;
Conduct competitor/market research and summarise insights;
Work with data from internal systems and support team communication.

What we look for:
University student or recent graduate in a technical, analytical, or business field (students from HSE, MIPT, Bauman, MSU, MEPhI, or SPbSTU are especially welcome);
Strong proactiveness and curiosity ‚Äî we value enthusiasm over experience;
Familiarity with Excel, and a basic understanding of APIs and how databases are structured;
Bonus if you have experience with SQL or any programming language;
Strong research and analytical thinking skills;
Intermediate English proficiency (Russian is a plus, but not required).

Internship details:
Format: Remote, you can join us from anywhere in the world
Duration: 3.07 - 31.07.2025
Time commitment: 4 hours/day (flexible schedule)
Type: Educational Internship ‚Äì Unpaid, with Structured Learning Opportunities

What we offer:
Hands-On Experience: Engage in real projects that align with your academic and career aspirations, allowing you to apply theoretical knowledge in practical settings.
Skill Development: Enhance both technical and soft skills, including communication, teamwork, and problem-solving, through structured tasks and collaborative efforts.
Mentorship: Benefit from guidance and feedback from seasoned professionals committed to your personal and professional development.
Networking Opportunities: Connect with industry experts and peers, expanding your professional network for future opportunities.
Flexible Scheduling: Accommodate your academic commitments with a flexible work schedule designed to promote work-life balance.
Comprehensive Feedback: Receive constructive evaluations to help you reflect on your progress and identify areas for improvement.
Certificate of Completion: Upon successful completion, receive a certificate recognising your contributions and achievements during the internship.

About the job
pawaTech is looking for a Data Analyst with a strong grasp of sports trading and betting, and an inherent passion for teamwork and a collaborative spirit. As a part of our Risk and Trading team, you will be responsible for preparing reports, identifying patterns in sports and betting data, and turning insights into actionable suggestions that support internal stakeholders.

About us:
pawaTech is a leading iGaming solutions provider, delivering sportsbook, casino, lottery, and player management software as a service. We power betPawa - Africa‚Äôs largest betting brand, operating across multiple markets.

Our platform is designed for scale, handling millions of active users across the web and mobile, processing thousands of transactions every second. With nearly a decade of industry expertise, we don‚Äôt just build software - we craft tailored solutions that drive innovation. Our expertise, commitment to quality, and client-focused approach make us a trusted partner in Africa and beyond.

What you‚Äôll be doing:
Preparing reports based on internal sports and betting data;
Searching for patterns and abnormalities that can support business decisions;
Creating presentations and reporting packs for internal teams;
Validating data and ensuring accuracy in all reporting tasks;
Responding to ad-hoc analysis requests and contributing to ongoing projects;
Collaborating with stakeholders to align reporting with business needs.

What makes you a great candidate:
Hands-on experience with sports trading, betting, or related data;
Confident working with SQL, Excel, Looker, and visualisation tools like Power BI or Tableau;
Understanding sports deeply, either as a fan or participant, and knowing how to spot patterns others might miss;
Curious, analytical, and comfortable working in a task-flow and ad-hoc environment;
Strong communication skills, capable of turning complex data into simple, valuable insights.

Why choose pawaTech?
We make an impact and contribute to shaping of the iGaming culture;
We offer growth inside dedicated teams of seniors and career prospects;
We embrace a modern technological stack and innovative approach;
We value balance - a flexible environment and team events are waiting for you;
We play it fair with compensation that recognises and backs your achievements and team budgets.


This job is accepting ongoing applications, and there is no application deadline.

At pawaTech, we are dedicated to building a welcoming and diverse workplace and invite applicants from all backgrounds, regardless of race, gender, age, or other protected characteristics. Our hiring process ensures fairness, objectivity, and respect for every applicant. Applicants are welcome to redact or omit information from their resumes that identifies their age, date of birth, or dates of attendance or graduation from educational institutions.

In compliance with EU GDPR standards and PDPA in Estonia, your personal data will be treated confidentially, used purely for recruitment, and accessible only to authorised hiring team members. To request data deletion, updates, or transfers, please reach out via data.protection@pawatech.com we will fulfil your request in accordance with applicable data protection laws.
